Job Title:     Sr Category Manager
Job Location:  NJ: Madison
Pay Rate:      competitive
Job Length:    full time
Start Date:    2007-08-16

Company Name:  Wyeth
Contact:       Wyeth
Phone:         email only
Fax:           email only

Description:   At Wyeth, we have a vision of leading the way to a healthier world. Weve committed ourselves to achieving this vision by making quality, integrity and excellence the hallmarks of our business. A Fortune 500 company and global leader in pharmaceuticals, consumer healthcare, and animal healthcare products, we know that our employees are who keep us on the cutting edge of innovative discoveries and superior customer service. To sustain and enhance our leadership position in the pharmaceutical industry, we continue to recruit, develop and motivate individuals whose skills, values, and work ethic will grow and improve our business.

As a Senior Category Manager, you will perform opportunity analysis to identify projects that will deliver significant cost savings/value improvement. You will develop and implement effective cost management programs to deliver year-on-year cost improvement, and will facilitate and lead cross-functional and cross-organizational sourcing initiatives in collaboration with other functional business departments and various facilities for key indirect expenditure categories relating to corporate services, professional services, and/or other general/administrative goods and services. You will provide a full range of seamless strategic sourcing support to client groups in the areas of HR Operations- Benefits Administration to include Health &amp; Welfare, Pension, and Savings  Administration, EAP, and Relocation. Develop and implement performance standards for major contracts with fees at risk to drive performance. You will map and analyze business processes and determine opportunities achieved through influencing supply and demand of services. You will be responsible for structuring and negotiating supply agreements and managing supplier relations and performance to ensure all identified savings/benefits are realized.  You will select, maintain, and manage a supplier base that is financially sound, technically competent, and strategically aligned. You will utilize e-sourcing technologies to develop Request for Information (RFIs), Request for Proposals (RFPs), Reverse Auctions, and compose Service Contracts, Supply Agreements, and AHTs as required.  You will develop programs to minimize transactional processing cost for non-critical items by utilizing automation, standardization, and consolidation.  You will provide training on Wyeth Sourcing Methodology and best procurement practices to stakeholders and team members to maximize the value received for our expenditures.  You will report cost management and monthly purchase activities, and will ensure compliance with purchasing policies and procedures, ethical practices, Wyeth values and adherence to relevant laws and regulations.  You will complete miscellaneous projects/duties as assigned.

This position requires a BS or BA in Business, Materials Management, Supply Chain Management, Technical or Engineering disciplines and 14 years experience in sourcing, manufacturing, materials management or relevant technical discipline or 12-14 years experience with a MS or 12 years experience with a MBA. Candidate must have strong analytical abilities, ability to assess large volume of data and develop concise summaries and assessments to determine plan forward, strong and effective negotiation skills, proven ability to execute tasks and objectives in excellent and timely manner, strong sense of intuition and ability to anticipate outcomes of actions, variables and decisions, excellent persuasion and presentation skills, strong oral and written communication skills, and the ability to effectively manage source selection projects and increasingly complex programs with minimal supervision.

Wyeth offers competitive compensation and benefits programs, including child-care subsidies, flex-time, business casual attire, educational assistance and professional development programs.

For more information and to apply online, please visit us at: www.wyeth.com/careers

